Differential diagnosis . The new species is most similar to
Scutacarus baloghi Mahunka, 1967
, described from Australia ( Mahunka 1967 ), by the absence of the claw on tibiotarsus I, blunt-ended setae c 1, 2 and setae ps 3 distinctly longer than ps 1, 2 . It can be distinguished from the latter by distinctly shorter setae f and h 1 , which are almost twice shorter than 4 b (vs. setae f and h 1 subequal to 4 b in
S. baloghi
), by setae h 1 shorter than distance h 1 - h 1 (vs. h 1 distinctly longer than distance h 1 - h
1 in
S. baloghi
), by setae e subequal to distance e-f (vs. e distinctly shorter than ef n
S. baloghi
), and by longer setae h 2 , which are longer than distance h 1 - h 2 (vs. h 2 shorter than distance h 1 - h
2 in
S . baloghi
).
